FBIS4-26130 "drchi118_c_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 Central Eurasia Lithuanian Prime Minister on Economic Cooperation Lithuanian Prime Minister on Economic Cooperation OW1806030694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0227 GMT 18 Jun 94 OW1806030694 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Vilnius, June 17 (XINHUA) -- Lithuanian Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius said today that the forthcoming visit to lithuania by Chinese Vice Premier Qian Qichen is expected to further enhance economic cooperation between the two countries. Slezevicius told XINHUA in an exclusive interview that Lithuania attaches great importance to developing ties with China as there exist great potentials for economic cooperation between the two countries. Reviewing the development of the Lithuania-China relations in recent years, he said Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas's successful visit to China last year strongly pushed forward the bilateral relations. Referring to his country's situation, the prime minister said, "Lithuania is now enjoying a stable political situation and its economy is turning for the better although we still face a lot of problems." He stressed that the inflation rate in Lithuania has been brought under control and has now dropped to 23 percent from 189 percent in March 1993, when the current government took office. He also urged businessmen from east and west, including those from China, to invest in Lithuania.
